# ADR-003: Local LLM Support as a First-Class Capability

Status: Accepted

Date: 2026-06-02

Decision Makers:
AgentForge Architecture Board

---

# Context

AgentForge is intended to operate across:

- Developer Laptops
- Small Teams
- Enterprises
- Air-Gapped Environments
- Regulated Industries

Examples:

- Healthcare
- Finance
- Government
- Defense

Many organizations cannot send sensitive data to public cloud providers.

A strategic decision is required regarding support for local models.

---

# Problem

Should AgentForge:

Option A

Support only cloud providers.

or

Option B

Support cloud providers and local models equally.

---

# Options Considered

## Option A — Cloud Only

Supported Providers

OpenAI

Anthropic

Gemini

Azure OpenAI

Advantages

Simple Architecture

Faster Initial Development

High Model Quality

---

Disadvantages

Vendor Lock-In

Privacy Concerns

Compliance Challenges

Internet Dependency

High Long-Term Cost

No Air-Gapped Support

Decision

Rejected

---

## Option B — Cloud + Local Models

Supported Providers

OpenAI

Anthropic

Gemini

OpenRouter

Ollama

LM Studio

vLLM

OpenAI-Compatible APIs

Advantages

Provider Independence

Data Privacy

Cost Optimization

Offline Operation

Enterprise Adoption

Future Flexibility

---

Disadvantages

Additional Testing

Model Quality Variability

More Provider Implementations

Decision

Accepted

---

# Decision

AgentForge will support local models as a first-class platform capability.

Local providers will be treated equally to cloud providers.

No runtime component may assume:

- Internet connectivity
- Cloud access
- Specific provider availability

---

# Strategic Importance

Local LLM support is not a feature.

It is a platform principle.

